The menu is very flexible with many preparations vegetarian with the option to add fish, seafood, chicken or veal. This allows for good variety and some personal creativity. While we enjoyed everything, the baked zucchini appetizer was especially well received. We passed on deserts because we were full! The wait staff was friendly, informative and very attentive. It used to come packed with shrimp and crab. In the past the sauce was always incredibly rich and flavorful but tonight it had no flavor and was extremely watery, essentially colored water is the best way to describe the taste. The calamari was rubbery and the kind you would find at a National chain vs a nicer Italian restaurant. Ended up simply eating the shrimp from the dish, a few bites of pasta and then just tossing the rest. At least the bread is still good.  Overall a very disappointing experience and let down after being excited to return. Wouldn’t recommend it to friends or family anymore.

This place is quite overrated, as I was very disappointed during my last visit (New Year's Eve 2018). Perhaps they deserve some credit for being one of the few restaurants open on NYE with the same menu, but that wasn't enough to make up for the other shortcomings, in my opinion.  Food - Mostly bland/flavorless. Bread was soft, but the olive oil/balsamic tasted like nothing, almost like it came from bottles left open for days. The bruschetta reminded me of a DIY college dorm dinner, with half-melted cheese and - once again, bland - tomatoes. Garlic bread also had half-melted cheese (the kind that comes off the entire piece with one bite like a plastic lid). Main course was a bit better (penne with tomato cream sauce), but nothing to write home about.  Service - The biggest letdown. I appreciate our waiter putting in slightly customized orders for us, but we had to remind him numerous times to bring practically everything from more bread to take home bags and wine glasses.  We asked for more oil for the bread, and he brought just a plate of oil without balsamic (not what we meant, but understandable). My water was not once refilled. Empty plates were not cleaned off without a lengthy delay. He brought us wine for tasting and promptly walked away, leaving us to taste it alone (shouldn't you stick around in case we don't like it?). He didn't smile, laugh or otherwise exchange pleasantries with us and instead maintained a stoic 'this is just a job' attitude the whole time.  Ambience - Probably the only redeeming quality. Very nice atmosphere, although hip hop music is probably not the most fitting for an Italian restaurant. Nice décor, bar alongside the comfy booths, etc.

While it breaks my heart to leave such a low rating because I've never been disappointed in the food here, the service tonight was beyond awful. We were rushed and interrupted from start to finish. First, we did not received the complementary bread until we specially asked for it when our entrees were being dropped off. Secondly, we had only gotten about halfway through our entrees before we were asked about placing a dessert order. When we said no, we were immediately given our check. Considering the check presenter it was placed standing between our dinner plates, we laid it down next to the wall, so we could enjoy our conversation while we continued eating. Immediately, our server, Ki, came back to the table and asked to cash us out. We stated that it was not ready yet, since we were still eating, alas, she remained until we fished out a credit card for her. After bringing back the receipt for us to sign, she began clearing all of our plates from the table. Typically I wouldn't haven't minded, but again, I was still eating my dinner. While picking up a forkful of food, Ki asked me to pass her the side plate next to the wall. Never in my life have I felt so rushed out of a restaurant—I mean, was that side plate so important to clear that I couldn't even finish my dinner first? Needless to say, the food was still as great at ever, but I'll see that I have a different server if I ever decide to eat at Olazzo again.

Oooooooh.... Olazzo used to be a fave date night spot for  my ex and I. The food is delicious and they even let you buy bread that is not quite done so you can finish baking it at home!! That in itself has always been a plus!

Never have I ever had such delicious Italian food before. This isn't some mediocre pseudo Italian restaurant like Olive Garden or even Macaroni Grill. Everything tastes homemade and authentic. Their eggplant/chicken parmesan is to die for. Their lasagna bolognese is also a solid choice. You don't necessarily need an appetizer if you don't want to shell out extra for it--they give you fresh bread served with oil and vinegar as well as a fresh appetizer salad--but I would suggest doing so anyway since it's so good. My favorites are the Arancini and their two Mozzarella covered bread appetizers, though I would like to try their seafood (can't since I go with my partner who has allergies). They have a well stocked bar, but don't be fooled by the massive amount of martinis on their cocktail menu--these aren't like any martinis you've had before. Most are lighter on the vodka and stronger on mixes of wine and other liquors, and all have a really unique flavor. The upside down pineapple tastes just like the cake, the espresso is the best little coffee martini, and anything they have with mint is so refreshing. They are on the pricey side and a bit hard to get to being in downtown Silver Spring, so I don't go often, but when I do I always enjoy myself. The atmosphere is so warm and relaxing but it also manages to feel so trendy. If you live in the area, this is a must-go  date location and a great place to catch a delicious dinner.

The atmosphere is great and the food is delicious. It's 99% carbs so if you're trying to be on any sort of diet, don't come here. But if you want pasta, gnochhi, or arancini, this is place to be in Silver Spring. They have a dim romantic atmosphere in an old-world feeling restaurant, and the service was fantastic.

Barf my guts out. More like, "NO-lazzo." This is SYSCO boxed food reheated by drop outs at its finest. My "chicken parmesan"  was breaded somewhere in a factory in the midwest, flash frozen, shipped in a semi with WOW written in the dust on the trailer and then freshly fried by a guy with tattoos on his face. It had the consistency of warmed raw fish and tasted like nothing more than generic brand spaghetti sauce– a lot of work for a 1/4 thick piece of factory farmed meat. If you're looking for fine Italian in Silver Spring, go to the next more expensive place. Olazzo isn't even Olive Garden in a fancy façade.

To top it all off, the parmesan was fake (the type of stuff you get in an aluminum can).

The food and service are excellent. Didn't have the best experience on my first visit but every other time since then it's been fantastic! Go with friends it's much better then eating alone at the small bar! This place is small an narrow so when it's busy it's a tight fit.

My wife got the calamari and it tasted pre-made like it came from a bag. It was awful. And they sat us in the very back corner where there's a blanket separating the outside air from my seats. It's 41 degrees outside! Terrible place.
The food was wonderful. Amazing service very quick and polite. Would recommend anyone to come here.
One of my favorite places to eat in Silver Spring, Great food, Great service and hands down the nicest environment in town.
Great food, nice atmosphere and friendly staff!
Great Italian food and they have 312 beer on draft!

Delicious food. Service was good and I enjoyed the atmosphere. Bartender was nice and they had a great selection of appetizers and drinks. Homemade sauce made the lasagna so tasty! Definitely recommend this one.

Love this restaurant! The drinks are awesome! The food is awesome! The service is top-notch. Been here several times. Great date night spot! The exposed brick, dark wood, and dimly lit candles make for a super romantic ambiance. In my experience, their clientele consists mostly of couples and young professionals. I always get the Shrimp Rosé which has penne pasta, a creamy tomato sauce, shrimp, and crabmeat. The portion sizes are huge! The dishes come with salad and bread. Highly recommend! #cityexperts

My only regret about Olazzo is that I didn't try it sooner.  The food was great and the atmosphere is casual while still intimate and inviting.  I had the fettuccini alfredo which was excellent.  I also enjoyed the meatball sliders as an appetizer.

I went to olazzo for the second time this week and it was just as good as I remember it being the time. It was my 2nd wedding anniversary dinner and we wanted to go somewhere cozy and close to home. Our food was very good and the service was also great. The server checked in just enough times to be attentive--yet not annoying. We were seated in the back room and it was a bit tight/cramped at our table. The tables could stand to be a little bigger to accommodate the large plates the food is served on. We had the calamari to start (yum) and I had chicken Alfredo and my husband had chicken parm...both were very tasty. I'll definitely be returning to olazzo in the future.

I've been a long-time fan of Olazzo's; the cozy atmosphere, the friendly staff, and the top-notch food make this a go-to favorite. Roberto and his brother Ricardo set out to feature the food their mother and grandmother made them, and you can taste the love they put in each and every dish. Their fastidiousness extends to  the rustic brick walls,  the wooden ceiling beams they built themselves, and the flat-screen TV-cum-fireplace is a smart and inviting feature. You won't find a bad item on the menu, and you'd be hard-pressed to leave without a smile on your face. Buon appetito!
Friendly staff. Delicious authentic Italian cuisine. Had the lasagna bolognese which was hearty and flavorful. Very cozy atmosphere.
Food was great - kind of tight inside with the seating, but the atmosphere is pretty good too. Whether out on a date or with the guys to watch a game - its comfortable

We went for an early dinner looking for an informal place.  The food was excellent. I had the baked penne with eggplant and mild suasage while my wife had the shrimp and crabe rose. Also, the bread was fresh and really good. The wiatress could not have been nicer.  We find it easy to park on the street, there always seems to be a space nearby. There is also pleny of public parking in lots. We'll come back.
Great place for a casual dinner our a nice night out.

Very average American-Italian food. Nothing like Italy! Too bad, because the bartender & waitstaff are very nice. But nothing distinguishes this place from all the other "plain vanilla" Italian places in the area.
Food is mediocre. Their martini selection is spectacular.
